# YouTube Automation (Local Pipeline)

This project generates YouTube content assets locally: ideas, scripts, titles,
descriptions, tags, thumbnail text, and shorts prompts. It is designed to work
offline by default with a simple template-based generator. You can later plug
in your preferred LLM provider if needed.

## Quick Start

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -e .
```

Generate ideas:

```bash
yt-automation ideas
```

Generate a full pack (idea + script + metadata + shorts + thumbnail text):

```bash
yt-automation run
```

Outputs are written to the `outputs/` folder.

## Configuration

Edit `config/channel.yaml` to set:

- Niche and audience
- Language and tone
- Video length and structure
- Upload cadence and style

Prompt templates live in `config/prompts/`.

## Optional LLM Provider

By default, the pipeline runs in `mock` mode and uses templates.
If you want to wire an API provider later, set:

```
LLM_PROVIDER=openai
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
```

This project includes a minimal OpenAI HTTP client in `src/yt_automation/llm.py`.
You can expand or replace it to fit your needs.

## Files

- `src/yt_automation/cli.py` CLI entrypoint
- `src/yt_automation/pipeline.py` main pipeline orchestration
- `config/channel.yaml` channel configuration
- `config/prompts/*.txt` prompt templates
